programme.title: AMOUR MORT
programme.desc: In France, domestic violence kills one woman every three days. A figure that reflects only part of the actual violence inflicted. 220,000 women declare suffering at the hands of their husband or partner. But how many daren't speak out? Anne, Florence, Agathe, Aude, Christelle, Graldine and Latifa tell their stories.

programme.title: LA PEINTURE FRANAISE AUTOUR DU MONDE
programme.desc: Founded in 1937, the National Gallery of Art, in Washington, is one of the world's most imposing museums by the importance of the works exhibited. The collections are shared between two buildings, linked by a gallery underneath the Mall. It houses some of the great French names in modern art.

programme.title: 64' LE MONDE EN FRANAIS - 1RE PARTIE
programme.desc: International current affairs as seen by the French-speaking world.

programme.title: 64' LE MONDE EN FRANAIS - 2E PARTIE
programme.desc: International current affairs as seen by the French-speaking world.

programme.title: L'INVIT
programme.desc: Patrick Simonin hosts the stars in the headlines, culture, music, film, books, an unmissable rendezvous with all those who light up our times.

programme.title: 64' L'ESSENTIEL
programme.desc: The whole world, in French.

programme.title: LA COURSE FOLLE
programme.desc: Have our fishermen chosen the best spots to set their traps, or will they need to rethink their strategy? Lobster fishing is a mad race against time where every decision counts, directly affecting the fishermen's income and their pride! And today mechanical problems are also lying in wait.

programme.title: LE JOURNAL DE LA RTBF
programme.desc: Complete international news roundup presented by the RTBF news staff.

programme.title: LES 100 LIEUX QU'IL FAUT VOIR
programme.desc: Pilgrims have crossed France since mediaeval times, heading for Santiago de Compostela. Our epic journey follows one of the four French routes leading to the Spanish sanctuary: the Voie de Vzelay, in deepest Burgundy. We stop off at the Saint Front cathedral in Prigueux before heading to the Pyrenees.

programme.title: SUR LE FRONT
programme.desc: France is committed to 10% of its territory being given reinforced protection. But what is the real situation? In Natura 2000 classified areas, pesticides can still be used; in Marseille, the city's sewers discharge into the Calanques... Investigation into the convenient compromises and concessions used to get around the regulations.

programme.title: LE JOURNAL DE LA RTS
programme.desc: All the news from RTS.

programme.title: LE JOURNAL DE FRANCE 2
programme.desc: The television news programme of the France 2 editorial board (8 p.m. edition, Paris time).

programme.title: LE 23H
programme.desc: The 11pm news bulletin (Paris time) by franceinfo. Discover the major news reports, interviews and analysis by the editorial team for an in-depth coverage of all the French and international current affairs.

programme.title: PLUS GRAND QUE SOI
programme.desc: At what point does a young person become the carer for an ill or disabled member of the family? We meet Alice, Cynthia, va and Martin, who discuss their lives as carers. With emotion, they share their experiences, both difficult and constructive, and talk about the virtues of empathy.

programme.title: L'CHAPPE BELGE
programme.desc: A bike journey, presented by Adrien Joveneau. With each programme, the presenter tells us of a stage in his journey and talks about mobility and tourist resources in the region.

programme.title: UN SI GRAND SOLEIL
programme.desc: The Bastide, Estrela, Salama, Lvy, Berville and Alami families, plus a host of supporting characters, live and work in the modern everyday city of Montpellier, in southern France. Between romance and crime thriller, with a blend of comic and serious themes, their stories weave a fascinating web.

programme.title: C JAMY
programme.desc: Kitchen, ornamental or medicinal, the garden is both useful and attractive. But when did it become an art form? What makes an English garden different from one '' la franaise''? How did the gardener Andr le Ntre get his reputation?

programme.title: ALEXANDRE DUMAS, LE FLAMBOYANT
programme.desc: A look back at ten years in the life of the French writer Alexandre Dumas (1802-1870).
